Problem 7.5

  1. It seems no change of the data when we execute the new one. The only thing change is that at before it is individual of First and Second, but now is the combination of First and Second.

  2. VoterData_B represent the total number of cases in this election while original Minneapolis2013 is the whole data frame with 5 variables

  3. VoterData_C grouped by the First and second and calculate the total number of the vote of the combination

4.Since the summarise function turns multiple cases into a single case using reduction functions. However, the group_by function is after it and it has been reduce. There are two cases. As a result, both first and second column can not be found.

VoterData_A <-
  Minneapolis2013 %>%
  group_by(First, Second)
VoterData_B <-
  Minneapolis2013 %>%
  summarise( total = n() )
VoterData_C <-
  Minneapolis2013 %>%
  group_by(First, Second) %>%
  summarise( total = n() )
